RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAN'T BE BROKEN stalked inside of foes from the two path, was nudged along rounding the turn, angled out to the six path turning into the stretch, and rallied to be up in the final sixteenth. SERGEANT SINATRA was prompted along in the five path, loomed from the four path passing the quarter, ran on to lead while back in the five path passing the eighth pole, but was caught by an outer foe in the final sixteenth to place. LOST CITY set the pace in the three path, was roused from the two path early around the turn, yielded to a pair of outer foes passing the eighth pole, but held show. GARY'S FLYING LION hit the inner part of the gate leaving, travelled off the pace in the three path, angled out to the seven path in upper stretch, but was one paced. MIRO trailed in the two path, was driven from said position into the stretch, but made no impact. SECRET SOLDIER rated in the four path, floated out around the turn and was in the six path at the top of the lane, altered back inwards but was no factor. TAPIT'S DIRECTION tracked in the three path, was floated out to the eight path in upper stretch, and did not threaten. NYQUEST NIX pressed in the four path, headed the leader from the three path passing the quarter, but weakened down the lane.
